Design and implement a Library Management System in Java that allows users to borrow books
and calculates their borrowing status. The program should take input for user details such as
name and ID, along with the number of books issued and the number of days for which the
books are borrowed. It should compute any late fine based on the number of extra days beyond
the allowed limit. The program should display the user details, list of books issued, and total
fine (if any).
• Create a GitHub repository for a Maven-based application following the standard
Maven directory structure [10]
• Clone this repository into VS Code, make the necessary code modifications, and
commit the changes back to the Git repository [10]
• Build and verify the application within VS Code to ensure it is compatible with
Jenkins integration [10]
• Finally, set up a Pipeline project in Jenkins and execute the CI/CD process by writing
and running the required pipeline script [20]
